      • filterActiveEntities

        public List<? extends EntityType> filterActiveEntities(String filterKey,
                                                       int maxRecords,
                                                       Integer accountDetailTypeId)
        Description copied from interface: EntityTypeService
        Returns the list of active entities filtered using the given filter key. This is mainly used for filtering entities to be shown in auto-complete boxes on UI. It is expected that the implementation of this method uses both the "name" and "code" to perform the filtering, and supports text searches (LIKE clause)
        Specified by:
        filterActiveEntities in interface EntityTypeService
        Parameters:
        filterKey - The filter key
        maxRecords - Maximum number of records to be returned. If this is passed as -1, the method should return all the records.
        accountDetailTypeId - The account detail type id
        Returns:
        List of filtered active entities
